    <item>
      <title>A Most interesting Item - Glowing Bone Helm</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancertactics&amp;message.id=906#M906</link>
      <description>What is this you might ask? Well for one thing Allakhazam's won't tell you and through some research of my own over serveral posts over the years I have discovered it is right under everyone's noses at of all places Kurn's Tower. Listen and learn.........&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Most people who have played Everquest are familiar with the Quest: Skull of Torture:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Skull Of Torture: LORE ITEM&lt;br&gt;Slot: NECK&lt;br&gt;AC+2 INT+5 HP+10 MANA+10 END+10 &lt;br&gt;Classes: All Classes&lt;br&gt;Races: Iksar Ogre Troll Gnome Dark Elf Barbarian Erudite Half Elf Human&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There is yet an additional item that can be obtained from the Skeletal Cook which is known as:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Glowing Bone Helm: &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;AC+18 WIS+7 INT+7 MR+10&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To my knowledge it is usable to the caster classes only&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When you kill the Skeletal Cook he drops a:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hollow Skull (4 Slot container)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There is a scroll that one can obtain in Kurn's mentioning a new Skull/Head to be fashioned and a few items are needed in order to do this:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;A Dried Tongue - Drops from a Burynai Forager.&lt;br&gt;A Dusty Sealed Canopic x2 (They are Lore so the only way to tell them apart is that you can carry both) - Also drops from the same Burynai.&lt;br&gt;A Glowing Mask - This is a very rare drop from the Skeletal Cook.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Once you aquire these items, you will need to travel to The Overthere Outpost and locate Galdorn Vok Nir who can be found at p3150, p2040. Ask him "What about the dusty sealed canopic jars?"&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When you do this he will take your Jar I believe one at a time, open them and return to you a "Preserved Eye." Once you have both eyes, you can take them and the previous items and combine them in the Hollow Skull for the Item listed above. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It seems to me that this might certainly be a nice item to obtain with very little effort as long as you can enter the OT safely. Any further input from people who may of done this is welcome and appreciated. I definately intend to seek this item out in the near future.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
