      <title>Soloing tips?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancertactics&amp;message.id=887#M887</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Hey all, &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've recently come back to the game and decided that the necromancer is the perfect class for me. I can only solo due to RL and so far I've been really having alot of fun with my necro and am looking foward to leveling him to 70. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But I'm level 26 now (dinged last night :)) and I've got a few questions. Remember I'm really new. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;First here's my Magelo. &lt;A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1315183" target=_blank&gt;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1315183&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;All my gear on it is current. I started from scratch with no help. So this was what I was able to buy after spending some time hunting silk. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I don't want to spend anymore time hunting silk. So I'm not interested in upgrading my gear if will cost me alot of plat. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I focused mainly on mana items. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So here are my questions. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. I have been able to level pretty quickly using the "hot zones" I simply pull with snare, send my pet in, throw in another dot which usally agro's mob, then I melee along with my pet and throw in my lifespikes. Then I sit and med and do it again. This works really well now but I know that it won't at higher levels. So I am trying to learn the different ways to solo. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. Agro kiting - I can't seem to do this right. I snare mob and throw in a dot and run...... I have my pet's taunt off and then I have it attack. So it hits on mob from behind while mob is chasing me. The only problem though, is that I've read posts saying that I run way ahead of mob and then sit and med. But I can't ever run way ahead of mob. Even with my darkness snare, I can never run so far ahead of mob to be able to sit and med. So basically I run around in circles while my pet hits from behind the whole time. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I don't really ever ask for buffs. So I don't ever get sow's. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Fear kiting - Ok, the only problem with FK is that my fear spell only works for a few ticks. This is pretty annoying and I really don't like to Fear Kite. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The main problem I'm seeing so far at level 26 with both types of kiting is that my pet simply doesn't do enough damage to make either type of kiting valid. My pet misses I would say at least 80% of the time on Blue mobs. This is really discouraging. Is this normal? I'm like wondering why my pet who is the same level or even a level or two above my single pulled mob misses so much in melee? I have all the buffs that I can put on him all the time. ( I dont remember the names ) spirit armour and the other pet buff that helps with melee. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But all I keep reading is Garn misses, Garn misses, Garn misses, Garn misses. So, here I am, trying to sit and med and fearing or running around in a huge circle waiting for my pet to kill the mob and it takes like half an hour because my stupid pet takes forever to land a hit. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So, that is why I've stuck to just pulling and meleeing and nuking. I land a couple of dots and then basically lifespike or tap which ever one for my level, I forgot. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Yes, I go oom after a couple of pulls, but waiting for mana to regen is almost as fast as waiting for pet to kill mob. So right now theres not much difference. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
