    <item>
      <title>Getting into Sebillis Crypt (Guide)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=necromancertactics&amp;message.id=878#M878</link>
      <description>I've printed this guide in numerous forms before on necro boards but&#xD;
it's been lost over and over again so I thought I would post it here in&#xD;
hopes that it might stick around.&amp;nbsp; This tactic works for getting&#xD;
through plenty of locked doors but this seems to be the easiest and&#xD;
safest to practice on because of the low level of the mobs and volume&#xD;
of them.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
First head to Sebillis and bind outside.&amp;nbsp; You might die the first&#xD;
couple of times and the run there takes quite a while otherwise.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
Running down and getting your body isn't really an issue if you know&#xD;
the way.&amp;nbsp; I used to just train down to the crypt entrance and wait&#xD;
for mobs to reset before I pulled my body off to a corner and&#xD;
looted/rezzed.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Once inside I buff up and make my pet and suspend him.&amp;nbsp; (Not&#xD;
required, but I like to have a pet on the ready to hold off a mob so I&#xD;
can posistion if need be).&amp;nbsp; Camp check and make sure no one is&#xD;
camping the Necrosis Scarab or the Sebilite Guardian so you don't train&#xD;
them.&amp;nbsp; You can make this run in 2 flops or just one depending on&#xD;
how well you know the run.&amp;nbsp; Run on with Sow if you don't have run&#xD;
5 and go down the hallway thru the door and down the corridor and&#xD;
across the area with the broken floor.&amp;nbsp; If you don't think you&#xD;
have enough HP or speed, you can have a pet up to let him take some&#xD;
agro from so mobs to buy you some time.&amp;nbsp; FD in the area past the&#xD;
broken floor but before the Necrosis Scarab.&amp;nbsp; Wait for mobs to&#xD;
reset and look in 3rd person to be sure a wandering froggy isn't&#xD;
there.&amp;nbsp; Here, you can either start pulling mobs single, or train&#xD;
down again to the door to the crypt. If this is your first time, I'd&#xD;
recommend killing your way down so you have some room to maneuver&#xD;
in.&amp;nbsp; The first pull of scarabs will bring 2, so you can root one&#xD;
and let the other come, or snare one and fd and let the other reset.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Kill your way down until you reach the entrance to the crypt.&amp;nbsp; The&#xD;
mob we are looking for is Sebilite Guardian.&amp;nbsp; Be sure to do some&#xD;
damage to the mob so you get on the summoning list.&amp;nbsp; The tactics&#xD;
are thus.&amp;nbsp; Have pet tank the mob, stacking on dots but NOT enough&#xD;
to kill the Guardian, keeping snare on the mob.&amp;nbsp; When he gets low&#xD;
on HP he'll turn to run.&amp;nbsp; At this point, I pocket my pet, or /pet&#xD;
get lost to remove him from the agro table.&amp;nbsp; the snared Golem will&#xD;
slowly walk toward the crypt and warp through the locked door.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
Once on the other side of the door, immediately root him and he'll&#xD;
summon you to him. At this point you can either tap tank him down, or&#xD;
FD once again to let him reset.&amp;nbsp; I'd recommend killing him if you&#xD;
can.&amp;nbsp; He can wander off and won't reset for some time.&amp;nbsp; You&#xD;
can even get a second person through if you FD and they are on the agro&#xD;
list, they'll get summoned next providing they did some previous damage&#xD;
and the Golem is still rooted.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Once through the door, mobs are mostly undead and it's a necro's&#xD;
paradise. Work your way down for camping all the named and loot that&#xD;
still sells decently.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Enjoy.&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
